@startuml
title ESP8266 Weather Station - Deployment Sequence Diagram

actor "System Admin" as Admin
participant "ESP8266 NodeMCU" as ESP8266
participant "Sensors" as Sensors
participant "MQTT Broker" as MQTT
participant "ThingSpeak Cloud" as ThingSpeak
participant "OpenWRT Router" as OpenWRT
participant "mosquitto-subscribe.sh" as MosqSub
participant "collectd" as Collectd
participant "RRDTool Database" as RRD
participant "collectd-rrdtool-publish.sh" as RRDPublish
participant "Cron Job" as Cron
participant "rrdtool-graph-github.sh" as GraphScript
participant "GitHub Repository" as GitHub
participant "Local HTTP Client" as HTTPClient

== System Boot and Initialization ==
Admin -> OpenWRT: Boot OpenWRT Router
activate OpenWRT
OpenWRT -> MosqSub: Start mosquitto-subscribe service (init.d)
activate MosqSub
MosqSub -> MQTT: Subscribe to ESP8266 topics
activate MQTT
OpenWRT -> Collectd: Start collectd service
activate Collectd
OpenWRT -> Cron: Configure daily cron job for graph generation
activate Cron

Admin -> ESP8266: Power on ESP8266 NodeMCU
activate ESP8266
ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Initialize sensors and WiFi
ESP8266 -> MQTT: Connect to MQTT Broker
ESP8266 -> ESP8266: Start local HTTP server

== Runtime Data Collection and Publishing ==
loop Periodic Sensor Reading
    ESP8266 -> Sensors: Read sensor data (temp, humidity, pressure, UV, etc.)
    activate Sensors
    Sensors --> ESP8266: Return sensor readings
    deactivate Sensors

    ESP8266 -> MQTT: Publish sensor data to ThingSpeak topic
    MQTT -> ThingSpeak: Forward data to ThingSpeak Cloud
    activate ThingSpeak
    ThingSpeak -> ThingSpeak: Store sensor data
    deactivate ThingSpeak

    ESP8266 -> MQTT: Publish sensor data to OpenWRT topic
    MQTT -> MosqSub: Deliver MQTT message
    MosqSub -> MosqSub: Save data to temporary files (/data/*.txt)
end

== Local HTTP Access ==
HTTPClient -> ESP8266: HTTP GET request for real-time readings
activate HTTPClient
ESP8266 --> HTTPClient: Return current sensor data (HTML)
deactivate HTTPClient

== Data Processing on OpenWRT ==
loop Collectd Processing Cycle
    Collectd -> RRDPublish: Execute collectd-rrdtool-publish.sh
    activate RRDPublish
    RRDPublish -> RRDPublish: Read data from temporary files (/data/*.txt)
    RRDPublish -> RRD: Update RRDTool database with sensor data
    activate RRD
    RRD --> RRDPublish: Confirm update
    deactivate RRD
    RRDPublish -> RRDPublish: Delete processed temporary files
    deactivate RRDPublish
end

== Daily Automated Graph Generation and Publishing ==
Cron -> GraphScript: Trigger daily execution
activate GraphScript
GraphScript -> RRD: Query historical sensor data
activate RRD
RRD --> GraphScript: Return time-series data
deactivate RRD
GraphScript -> GraphScript: Generate graphs using RRDTool
GraphScript -> GraphScript: Commit graph images to local Git repository
GraphScript -> GitHub: Push updated graphs to remote repository
activate GitHub
GitHub --> GraphScript: Confirm successful push
deactivate GitHub
deactivate GraphScript

== Continuous Operation ==
note over ESP8266, GitHub
    System continues to collect, publish, process,
    and visualize sensor data continuously.
    Daily cron job ensures historical graphs
    are updated and published to GitHub.
end note

deactivate Cron
deactivate Collectd
deactivate MosqSub
deactivate MQTT
deactivate OpenWRT
deactivate ESP8266

@enduml
